p.span: Philosophies driving instruction at the All Aboard Charter School will rely on a developmentally appropriate approach which will have students actively involved in the learning process. We will build on the student’s prior knowledge and their personal interest through a creative approach. We will use a literature-based curriculum with an emphasis on language arts and math. The school will use a variety of instructional methods to deliver the curriculum to the students including but not limited to; direct instruction, small group lessons, whole group lessons, individual lessons, experiential learning opportunities and free exploration. The students will also be guided through creative opportunities such as; sharing, calendar activities, and center choice time with a focus on language arts, math, and music. We will use the methods proven through research to successfully reach the learning styles and needs of all students. We will work to integrate the other core areas of the Arizona State Standards.

The All Aboard Charter School strives to prepare children to be productive in their environment, have a high quality of education, involve the parents and the community, to enhance the safe learning environment of students and to have a strong emphasis on literacy and reading.

div.p: Looking for an alternative to public school? Your children deserve the best education in Phoenix and our teachers are here to deliver the best!

h6.span: Per A.R.S. § 38-431.01 & 02. of meetings for All Aboard Charter School will be posted on this website under Public Meeting Notice. Meeting dates and notices will also be posted in the front window at 5827 N. 35th Ave, Phoenix, AZ. 85017.
